ZH: 我刚好在这个地方看见了她。
EN: I just happened to see her at this place.

ZH: 刚好下雨，我带了伞。
EN: It just started raining, and I brought my umbrella.

ZH: 昨天的钱刚好够了。
EN: The money from yesterday was just enough.

ZH: 他刚好坐在我旁边。
EN: He happened to be sitting right next to me.

ZH: 刚好在这条路上有一个小商店。
EN: There happens to be a small shop on this road.

ZH: 她的电话刚好关机。
EN: Her phone just happened to be off.

ZH: 我们刚好错过了火车。
EN: We just missed the train.

ZH: 他们刚好向我们走来。
EN: They happened to be walking towards us.

ZH: 刚好有一个空座位。
EN: There happens to be an empty seat.

ZH: 我们刚好能看到演出的最后一场。
EN: We were able to catch the last showing of the performance.

ZH: 刚好到了下课的时间。
EN: It just happened to be time for class to end.

ZH: 他刚好说出了我的想法。
EN: He just happened to say what I was thinking.

ZH: 刚好想起了你的生日。
EN: I just happened to remember your birthday.

ZH: 这里的风刚好凉爽。
EN: The wind here just happens to be cool.

ZH: 我们刚好拥有足够的资源。
EN: We happen to have enough resources.

ZH: 他们刚好能赶上末班车。
EN: They just happened to catch the last bus.

ZH: 刚好发现了一个新的餐馆。
EN: Just happened to discover a new restaurant.

ZH: 那颗树刚好挡住视线。
EN: That tree just happens to block the view.

ZH: 他们刚好错过了飞机。
EN: They just happened to miss the plane.

ZH: 我刚好需要一支笔。
EN: I happen to need a pen.
